source: All @provider data is intelligently and automatically cached using the various settings below. This allows the @provider data to persist through cache rebuilds. This data will invalidate and rebuild automatically, however a manual reset can be invoked below.

All caching is forced to "Forever" when using the "Custom" CDN Provider. This is because the provided Custom URLs above are used as part of the cache identifier. Anytime the above Custom URLs are modified, all of the caches are rebuilt automatically.

All external HTTP requests initiated by this theme are subject to caching. Cacheability is determined automatically based on a manually passed TTL value by the initiator or if there is a "max-age" response header present. These cached requests will persist through cache rebuilds and will only be requested again once they have expired. If you believe there is some request not being properly retrieved, you can manually reset this cache here.
Allows the use of any CDN by providing the ability to manually specify a repository of available URLs.

target: Es ist ein Fehler aufgetreten bei dem Versuch das Theme @theme_title zu aktualisieren.

source: Appends the popover to a specific element. Example: body. This option is particularly useful in that it allows you to position the popover in the flow of the document near the triggering element - which will prevent the popover from floating away from the triggering element during a window resize.

source:
Elements that have the data-toggle="popover" attribute set will automatically initialize the popover upon page load.
WARNING: This feature can sometimes impact performance. Disable if pages appear to hang after load.

Elements that have the data-toggle="tooltip" attribute set will automatically initialize the tooltip upon page load.
WARNING: This feature can sometimes impact performance. Disable if pages appear to "hang" after load.

Enable the .well, .well-sm or .well-lg classes for specified regions.
Enable this setting if you wish to suppress deprecated warning messages.
Enabling this focuses on the first available and visible input found in the modal after it's opened. If no element is found, the close button (if visible) is focused instead.

Enabling this replaces the core/jquery.ui.dialog dependency in the core/drupal.dialog library with a jQuery UI Dialog widget bridge. This bridge adds support to Bootstrap Modals so that it may interpret jQuery UI Dialog functionality.
Enabling this selects the text of the first available and visible input found after it has been focused.
Enabling this setting will include any deprecated.php file found in your theme or base themes.
target: Bei Aktivieren dieser Einstellung werden alle deprecated.php Dateien, die zum Theme oder Basis-Theme gehören, mit eingeschlossen.

source: If a selector is provided, tooltip objects will be delegated to the specified targets.
If a selector is provided, tooltip objects will be delegated to the specified targets. In practice, this is used to enable dynamic HTML content to have popovers added.
If an element has a .has-error class attached to it, enabling this will automatically remove that class when a value is entered.
target: Wenn an ein Element eine .has-error-CSS-Klasse angehängt wurde, wird bei Aktivieren dieser Option die Klasse automatisch entfernt, sobald ein Wert eingegeben wurde.

source: If an element in a form is required, enabling this will always display the element with a .has-error class. This turns the element red and helps in usability for determining which form elements are required to submit the form.

If enabled, the active popover will automatically close when it loses focus, when a click occurs anywhere in the DOM (outside the popover), the escape key (ESC) is pressed or when another popover is opened.

source: Images in Bootstrap 3 can be made responsive-friendly via the addition of the .img-responsive class. This applies max-width: 100%; and height: auto; to the image so that it scales nicely to the parent element.

source: Insert HTML into the popover. If false, jQuery's text method will be used to insert content into the DOM. Use text if you're worried about XSS attacks.

source: Inspired by the excellent jQuery.tipsy plugin written by Jason Frame; Tooltips are an updated version, which don't rely on images, use CSS3 for animations, and data-attributes for local title storage. See Bootstrap tooltips for more documentation.

One complete URL per line. All URLs are validated and parsed to determine available version(s) and/or theme(s). A URL can be any file ending in .css or .js (with matching response MIME type). Minified URLs can also be supplied and the will be used automatically.

source: Wraps tables with .table-responsive to make them horizontally scroll when viewing them on devices under 768px.
